<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI" id=queryme-vs-queryuser><code>Query.me</code> vs <code>Query.user</code><a href=#queryme-vs-queryuser class=hash-link aria-label="Direct link to queryme-vs-queryuser" title="Direct link to queryme-vs-queryuser" translate=no>​</a></h2>
<p>When working with permissions in Saleor, it's important to understand:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong><code>Query.me</code></strong> returns the <em>effective permissions</em> of the currently authenticated user,
as encoded in the access token. This includes permissions granted dynamically, such as through Single Sign-On (SSO)
or Role-Based Access Control (RBAC). These may not be stored on the User object in the database.</li>
<li class=""><strong><code>Query.user</code></strong> returns only the permissions stored for a specific user in the database.
It does <em>not</em> include any permissions granted dynamically.</li>
</ul>
